Organizations should implement policies for information security by establishing clear procedures and responsibilities. Regular review and updates should be conducted to ensure continued effectiveness. Consider organizational context, risk assessment results, and applicable legal requirements.

nodes.purpose: To detect and prevent the unauthorized disclosure and extraction of information by individuals or systems.
nodes.name: Data leakage prevention

nodes.purpose: To limit the exposure of sensitive data including PII, and to comply with legal, statutory, regulatory and contractual requirements.
nodes.name: Data masking

nodes.purpose: To prevent unnecessary exposure of sensitive information and to comply with legal, statutory, regulatory and contractual requirements for information deletion.
nodes.name: Information deletion

nodes.purpose: To ensure hardware, software, services and networks function correctly with required security settings, and configuration is not altered by unauthorized or incorrect changes.
nodes.name: Configuration management

nodes.purpose: To ensure only authorized access and to prevent unauthorized access to information and other associated assets.
nodes.name: Information access restriction

nodes.purpose: To ensure only authorized users, software components and services are provided with privileged access rights.
nodes.name: Privileged access rights

nodes.purpose: To protect information against the risks introduced by using user endpoint devices.
nodes.name: User endpoint devices

nodes.purpose: To ensure the availability of the organization’s information and other associated assets during disruption.
nodes.name: ICT readiness for business continuity

nodes.purpose: To specify and manage information security for the use of cloud services.
nodes.name: Information security for use of cloud services

nodes.purpose: To provide awareness of the organization’s threat environment so that the appropriate mitigation actions can be taken.
nodes.name: Threat intelligence

nodes.purpose: To ensure management understand their role in information security and undertake actions aiming to ensure all personnel are aware of and fulfil their information security responsibilities.
nodes.name: Management responsibilities

nodes.purpose: To reduce the risk of fraud, error and bypassing of information security controls.
nodes.name: Segregation of duties

nodes.purpose: To establish a defined, approved and understood structure for the implementation, operation and management of information security within the organization.
nodes.name: Information security roles and responsibilities

nodes.purpose: To ensure continuing suitability, adequacy, effectiveness of management direction and support for information security in accordance with business, legal, statutory, regulatory and contractual requirements.
nodes.name: Policies for information security
Physical controls
nodes.description: Controls related to physical security, facilities, and equipment.

nodes.name: Organizational controls
nodes.description: Controls related to the organization's structure, policies, and management.
